  "title": "Cloud Platform Lead",
  "description": "<p><strong>Our Client is looking for a cloud engineer to lead and manage cloud service delivery. </strong></p><p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><p><br /></p><ul><li>Lead and manage onboarding process of new AWS accounts from request intake to production readiness. </li><li>Work closely with application and business teams to understand requirements and timelines.</li><li>Act as the liaison between application teams, cloud engineering and security teams to ensure new AWS accounts are provisioned, configured, and handed over to operations with compliance, security, and governance fully in place.</li><li>Oversee AWS account creation via Control Tower Account Factory.</li><li>Ensure baseline controls (GuardDuty, Security Hub, IAM Identity Center, CloudTrail, etc.) are enforced as part of Infrastructure as Code.</li><li>Ensure that network connectivity (VPC, Transit Gateway, etc.) and restrictions are correctly applied.</li><li>Provide onboarding status updates to stakeholders and management.</li><li>Collaborate with DevOps teams to embed automation pipelines for account setup.</li></ul><p></p><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Experience in enterprise scale IT operations, cloud service delivery, or project management (AWS experience preferred).</li><li>Strong understanding of AWS Control Tower, AWS Organizations, IAM, networking, and core security services.</li><li>Familiarity with CIS Benchmarks, AWS Well-Architected Framework, and security best practices.</li><li>Experience in Infrastructure-as-Code (Terraform, CloudFormation); CI/CD pipelines (Jenkins, GitLab CI); Security & compliance (IAM, Security Hub, AWS Config).</li></ul><p>To Apply or find out more information on this role, please email us or send in your updated resume to: shelly.tan@starcareerconsulting.com</p><p><br /></p><p>Shelly Tan Bee Leng (Reg. No. R2199458)</p><p>STAR CAREER CONSULTING PTE LTD (EA License: 20C0353)</p>",
